1 16–410.
2 (a) The Board of Community College Trustees for Howard County consists of
3 [seven] NINE members appointed by the [Governor] HOWARD COUNTY SENATE
4 DELEGATION with the advice and consent of the Senate.
5 (b) Of the members, at least [six] EIGHT:
6 (1) Shall be residents of Howard County at the time of appointment; and
7 (2) Shall maintain residency in Howard County throughout the term of
8 appointment.
9 (C) EACH MEETING OF THE BOARD SHALL INCLUDE AN OPPORTUNITY FOR
10 PUBLIC COMMENT.
11 (D) (1) THE BOARD SHALL MAKE A VIDEO OR AUDIO RECORDING OF EACH
12 MEETING OF THE BOARD.
13 (2) THE BOARD SHALL MAKE A RECORDING REQUIRED UNDER
14 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC ON THE BOARD’S
15 WEBSITE WITHOUT CHARGE AND, TO THE EXTENT PRACTICABLE, WITHIN 12 HOURS
16 AFTER THE RECORDING IS MADE.
17 (E) (1) EVERY 2 YEARS, THE BOARD MEMBERS SHALL UNDERGO
18 TRAINING ON THE PURPOSE OF A BOARD OF TRUSTEES.
19 (2) THE TRAINING REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS
20 SUBSECTION SHALL BE PROVIDED BY AN INDEPENDENT NONPROFIT
21 ORGANIZATION.
22 (F) EACH YEAR, THE BOARD SHALL SELECT AN INDEPENDENT,
23 NATIONALLY RECOGNIZED SURVEY INSTRUMENT TO CARRY OUT AN ANONYMOUS
24 SURVEY ON EMPLOYEE SATISFACTION AT HOWARD COMMUNITY COLLEGE, AND
25 SUBMIT AN UNEDITED REPORT ON ITS SURVEY FINDINGS DIRECTLY TO THE BOARD.
26 16–410.1.
27 (A) BEFORE THE BOARD OF COMMUNITY COLLEGE TRUSTEES FOR
28 HOWARD COUNTY RENEWS THE CONTRACT OF THE CURRENT HOWARD COMMUNITY
29 COLLEGE PRESIDENT, THE BOARD SHALL:
30 (1) OPERATE IN AN OPEN AND TRANSPARENT MANNER REGARDING
31 THE POTENTIAL CONTRACT RENEWAL;

