1 (2) PROVIDE OPPORTUNITY FOR PUBLIC COMMENT; AND
2 (3) SOLICIT PUBLIC FEEDBACK.
3 (B) NOTWITHSTANDING THE TERMS OF THE CONTRACT, FOR EACH
4 CONTRACT FOR THE POSITION OF HOWARD COMMUNITY COLLEGE PRESIDENT
5 EXECUTED ON OR AFTER JULY 1, 2025, THE COMPENSATION FOLLOWING
6 TERMINATION OF THE CONTRACT SHALL BE:
7 (1) IF 1 YEAR OR LESS REMAINS ON THE CONTRACT, EQUAL TO THE
8 COMPENSATION SET FOR THAT REMAINING TIME PERIOD; OR
9 (2) IF GREATER THAN 1 YEAR REMAINS ON THE CONTRACT, EQUAL TO
10 1 YEAR’S COMPENSATION PLUS 1 MONTH’S COMPENSATION FOR EACH ADDITIONAL
11 FULL YEAR REMAINING ON THE CONTRACT.
12 (C) ON OR BEFORE JANUARY 1, 2026, AND EACH 6 MONTHS THEREAFTER
13 UNTIL JULY 1, 2028, THE BOARD OF COMMUNITY COLLEGE TRUSTEES FOR
14 HOWARD COUNTY SHALL SUBMIT A REPORT TO THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY, IN
15 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, ON THE
16 STATUS OF THE FACULTY UNION CONTRACT.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the initial terms of the two
18 additional appointed members of the Board of Community College Trustees for Howard
19 County, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act, shall expire as follows:
20 (1) one member in 2032; and
21 (2) one member in 2033.
22 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
23 1, 2025.

